      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Azulene, a beautiful blue hydrocarbon, is an isomer of naphthalene. Is azulene aromatic? Draw a second resonance form of azulene in addition to that shown.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaVVWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--ac8956beca58bd2910e2e5da5e08b859d108ffc2/OChem_15_06_007.jpg\" alt=\"Azulene has a seven-carbon ring with three double bonds fused to a cyclopentadiene ring.\">",
      "answers": [],
      "hints": [],
      "formats": [
        "free-response"
      ],
      "combo_choices": [],
      "collaborator_solutions": [
        {
          "images": [],
          "solution_type": "detailed",
          "content_html": "<p>Yes, it's aromatic.</p>\n<img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaVlWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--8afdf7fe0a70a56145e48f7f18054627a43461f4/OChem_15_EC_206.jpg\" alt=\"Two resonance structures of azulene, separated by a double-headed arrow.\">"
